rComments: I took this class (Biology of Human Behavior) because it sounded very interesting. Professor Clancy somehow manages to make every class extremely boring. She loves to hear herself speak, treats students like children, and is overwhelmingly feminist. Luckily, this years class has no tests (only projects) and is half online

Looooves to hear herself talk. Makes a big deal about being 'professor clancy' while she is an assistant.  Really disconnected and most of her rants are about how you should under no circumstances attempt to contact her or email her because her time is too precious for students
very dedicated and knowledgeable teacher, expected a lot but definitely knew what she was talking about

You have to go to class to get your iClicker points, however they aren't worth much of your grade... so if you have a high A don't bother! She is kind of a snobby teacher, but the class is interesting and has reasonable expectations!

Definitely the worst gen-ed teacher at the U of I. She thinks she's God's gift to mankind by taking part in rallies, etc. The material is very interesting, but she just makes the class a tad too(x100) boring. She treats you like a child. And she is weirdly obsessed with cats and her daughter( though the latter is cute).avoid this class if possible.

The material is very interesting and the readings aren't as bad as people say.  She, however, is pretty unhelpful.  I saw her during office hours and that was a truly intimidating experience and even though I saw she was on Facebook, when I walked in she tried her hardest to get me out...quickly.

Managed to keep lecture in check, clearly very invested in materials she teaches, and material had refreshing women's studies slant. She's not "borderline" feminist. She IS feminist. Great class. Loved her.

Caring, kind prof. She cares about each student. She calls out students so that the ones who actually CARE about the class can hear and learn. She is not the LEAST bit mean. She is approachable, kind, and helpful. If you're confused about something, go to her office hours. She is incredibly helpful and tries way more than most profs.

Easy to get A/B, but not a blowoff class. Notes are online but very hard to follow if you dont go to lecture. She uses iClicker for points everyday. quizzes are worded weirdly sometimes, and she takes content from readings and class.  Tests were pretty reasonable, and take advantage of extra credit! good teacher, but as a person a little pushy
It was refreshing to have a professor who was clearly well educated and passionate about what she was teaching for a gen ed class. Interesting material from an expert, do take.

She is really full of herself and is borderline feminist. Lectures can be at times interesting, but not mandatory. Intelligent in area to some extent, but can say some pretty disagreeable things, especially to men. Her LOLcats are ridiculous and distractingly unfunny.

She is really mean and is not afraid to call you out for talking in a 700-person lecture hall. She is passionate and knowledgeable in her subject area, though. And she wears really cute clothes. The class is definitely interesting.

Clancy doesn't seem to care if you pass or fail her class. She's just there to hear herself talk. She won't answer any student's questions, you have to email a faceless TA (I say faceless b/c you see them once at the beginning of the semester when she introduces them and never again). This class was way hard for just a gen ed.

Attendance to lectures is not mandatory but you will be LOST if you don't go, not a blow-off. A majority of the questions on the exams are from the online quizzes to try to do well and study those.  If you don't have to take the class, don't! Not an easy gen-ed and very boring unless you are really interested in monkeys!!
She always tells us to shut up and it's annoying

She is passionate about what she does, and tries to make the class interesting. However she has a chip on her shoulder and it shows she has a need for everyone to pay attention to her. Lectures are in general useless and the quizzes are not from lecture or reading at times. Tests are fair.

She is one of the best professors I've had.  She makes everything easy to understand, and I came away learning a lot.  The exams were easy.  You can tell that she is very passionate about what she does.  I'd love to take another class with her.
incredibly intelligent, funny, and nice woman.  she made this class highly relevant and interesting.  go to class, and the material will stick.
Go to class; you get to see her and learn something.

This huge lecture class made Professor Clancy only care about her Honors Section rather the rest of the 600 students.  She provides all of the lecture notes online, so you would only need to report to the lectures three times for the three exams.  Also, 6 easy online quizzes are added to your grade.
